cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper is about learning undirected graphical models or Markov random fields (MRFs), which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a regret bound from the Hedge algorithm, which is a topic in online learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The algorithm's running time and sample complexity are also important aspects, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper's application to learning sparse Generalized Linear Models (GLMs) suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
